<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>polyval  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Stixbox Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>Nov 2001  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="polyval"> Polynomial evaluation  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y = polyval(p,x,s)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[y,delta] = polyval(p,x,s)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>p  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : vector. 
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>x  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : scalar, vector or matrix. 
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>s  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : see polyfit (second returned argument)
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    Polynomial evaluation. 
    If p is a vector of length d+1 whose elements are the coefficients of
    a polynomial, then y = polyval(p,x) is the value of the polynomial,
    defined by its 
    coefficients p, evaluated at x.
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
 y = p(1)*x^d + p(2)*x^(d-1) + ... + p(d)*x + p(d+1)
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    if x is a matrix or vector, the polynomial is evaluated at all
    points in x.
  </P>
  <P>
    [y,delta] = polyval(p,x,s) uses the optional output generated by
    polyfit to generate error estimates, y +/- delta.
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
</MAN>
